f</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19770320/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Is+breast+MRI+helpful+in+the+evaluation+of+inconclusive+mammographic+findings%3F&amp;author=L+Moy&amp;author=K+Elias&amp;author=V+Patel&amp;publication_year=2009&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=986-993&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.08.1229&amp;pmid=19770320">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">4.</div><div id="r4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Spick C, Szolar DHM, Preidler KW, Tillich M, Reittner P, Baltzer PA. Breast MRI used as a problem-solving tool reliably excludes malignancy. <em>Eur J Radiol</em> 2015;84(1):61–64.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ejrad.2014.10.005">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25454098/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Breast+MRI+used+as+a+problem-solving+tool+reliably+excludes+malignancy&amp;author=C+Spick&amp;author=DHM+Szolar&amp;author=KW+Preidler&amp;author=M+Tillich&amp;author=P+Reittner&amp;author=PA+Baltzer&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Eur+J+Radiol&amp;pages=61-64&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.ejrad.2014.10.005&amp;pmid=25454098">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Bluemke DA, Gatsonis CA, Chen MH, et al. Magnetic resonance imaging of the breast prior to biopsy. <em>JAMA</em> 2004;292(22):2735–2742.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1001/jama.292.22.2735">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed">